reviews.review_text:
Nice upgrade There is a real sweet audience of this show where the crowd energy really shines through, but this is a great upgrade.  
Could be the best show of this run, but the 1st set has kind of a lackluster list.  Some very sweet stuff follows.  China>Rider appeared on a Dead Zone way back in the late 80s I believe.  The LL Rain is really soulful, Very cool how Spoonful carries into the Drums, and the Space>Other One is transcendent.  Healy is workin' it hard, and the Boys shine to the end.  They argue about the encore a little.  Fun to hear.
